1. Authentication & Authorization

 Redirect unauthorized users on client-side (done ✅ but refine UX with nice error/403 page).

 Use Supabase session (supabase.auth.getSession) in getServerSideProps for server-side protection.

2. Database Security (Supabase RLS)

 Enable Row Level Security (RLS) on users and booking-related tables.

 Add policies:

users table → Users can select/update only their own row.

bookings table → Users can select/insert/update/delete only their own bookings.

Admins (role = admin) → Full access.

3. API Routes (if using Next.js API)

 Create serverless API routes (e.g. /api/admin/*) for sensitive admin actions.

 In those routes, verify session + role before performing DB queries.

4. Data Validation & Input Handling

 Validate booking forms on both client and server.

 Sanitize all text inputs (avoid malicious scripts).

5. Deployment & Secrets

 Store Supabase service role key & other API keys in server-side env vars (.env.local), never in client code.

 Configure production Supabase project to disallow anon key misuse (limit rate, enable RLS).

6. Admin UX

 Show 403 Unauthorized page when a non-admin tries to access admin pages.

 Add audit logs (optional) — record important admin actions like deleting bookings.

🔐 Bonus (Optional but Recommended)

 Rate-limit booking submissions to prevent spam.

 Add email verification step before first booking.

 Enable HTTPS (handled automatically by Vercel/Netlify if deployed).
